The paper deals with algorithms for tree inclusion, which is a problem in data structures and algorithms. The use of dynamic programming and the study of restricted variants suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), or machine learning (cs.LG).
